No ITypeHierarchyChangedListener#typeHierarchyChanged(..) event is sent when I add a type with a parametrized supertype.

Steps:
- paste into Package Explorer:

abstract class AAAList extends java.util.ArrayList&lt;String&gt; { }
abstract class AAAListRaw extends java.util.ArrayList { }

- comment both lines
- open Type Hierarchy on ArrayList
- uncomment one of the lines and save the editor

=&gt; When I uncomment the type AAAListRaw, the Type Hierarchy view is updated and shows the new subtype. OTOH, when I uncomment AAAList, the TH is not refreshed.

The bug is in 
org.eclipse.jdt.internal.core.hierarchy.TypeHierarchy.subtypesIncludeSupertypeOf(IType): &quot;type.getSuperclassName()&quot; and &quot;type.getSuperInterfaceNames()&quot; include the type arguments, but hasSubtypeNamed(String) expects a raw type.</thetext>
